Interface TlsCsr

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, TlsCsrTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TlsCsrStub

    public interface TlsCsr
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, TlsCsrTypes
    The TlsCsr interface provides methods to generate certificate signing request. This interface was added in vSphere API 6.7.2.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        TlsCsrTypes.Info create(TlsCsrTypes.Spec spec)
        Generates a CSR with the given Spec. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.2.

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        spec - The information needed to create a CSR.
        Returns:
        A Certificate Signing Request.
        Throws:
        Error - If CSR could not be created for given spec for a generic error.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires CertificateManagement.Manage and CertificateManagement.Administer.
